        <main class="container">
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>At ReadRecall, our mission is to enhance your reading experience by providing a platform to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Keep detailed notes on the non-fiction books you read.</li>
                <li>Rate and review books based on your personal preferences.</li>
                <li>Track your reading progress and easily revisit key insights.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Features</h3>
            <h4>Note-Taking Made Easy</h4>
            <p>Say goodbye to scattered notes! ReadRecall allows you to jot down your thoughts, key takeaways, and favorite quotes from each book, creating a digital library of your reading journey.</p>
     
            <h4>Rating System</h4>
            <p>Easily rate and review books on a scale of 0 to 10, helping you keep track of your favorites and share recommendations with the ReadRecall community.</p>
      
            <h4>Sorting and Filtering</h4>
            <p>Sort your book collection by rating, recency, or title, making it effortless to find the next book to dive into or revisit old favorites.</p>

            <h4>Getting Started</h4>
            <p>Ready to start organizing your reading experience? Sign up or log in to get started with ReadRecall.</p>

            <h4>Meet the Team</h4>
            <p>ReadRecall is a capstone project developed by Hari Haran. We are passionate about creating tools that enhance the reading journey and help readers get the most out of their books.</p>

            <h4>Contact Us</h4>
            <p>Have questions, suggestions, or just want to say hello? Feel free to contact us. We'd love to hear from you!</p>
